name: I Put a Spell on You
Sweet Soul Music
comments: Athur Conley just wanted to cover "Yeah Man", but when he sat down with Otis Redding, Otis decided to change the lyrics and retitle the song. Although the music is basicly the same as "Yeah Man", Sam Cooke wasn't credited as composer. He wasn't even mentioned in the new lyrics which paid tribute to many soul legends, including Otis Redding himself.
